🔴 Group 3: Major Projects (Nuclear Zone)
#1 — Migrate LEGACY SERVICE users away from password-only sign-ins

Severity: Critical | Scanner: Security Essentials
Current State: Legacy service accounts still authenticate via password only — no key pair, no OAuth. Front door key left in the lock.
Remediation:

Inventory all legacy service users
Generate RSA key pair per account
ALTER USER ... SET RSA_PUBLIC_KEY
Update application connection strings to use key pair auth
ALTER USER ... SET PASSWORD = NULL after validation
Apply network policy to restrict source IPs


Difficulty: Hard — requires multi-team coordination across every consuming app
Side-Effect Score: 8/10
Remediation Risk: Any missed app connection breaks production. Worst case: Critical ETL pipeline silently fails, downstream reports go stale, business decisions made on bad data.
Risk of Not Fixing: Password can be brute-forced, phished, or reused from other breaches. Worst case: Attacker logs in as service account, exfiltrates customer PII to dark web.

Prerequisites: Weak/leaked password • No network policy • No anomalous login detection


Audit Exception: Service slated for retirement by [date]; compensating controls in place — IP allowlist, login alerts, 90-day password rotation.

