#12 — Human users with passwords not subject to MFA enrollment policy

Severity: Medium | Scanner: Security Essentials
Current State: Some/all human users authenticating via password are not bound to an authentication policy requiring MFA. In 2026, this is hiking Everest in flip-flops.
Remediation:

CREATE AUTHENTICATION POLICY require_mfa SET MFA_AUTHENTICATION_METHODS=('TOTP') SET CLIENT_TYPES=(...)
Apply at account level: ALTER ACCOUNT SET AUTHENTICATION POLICY require_mfa
Notify users to enroll (Duo/TOTP)
Define grace period, then enforce


Difficulty: Med — technically simple, change management is the hard part
Side-Effect Score: 5/10
Remediation Risk: Users locked out if they don't enroll in time → helpdesk ticket flood. Worst case: Mass lockout disrupts business; leadership escalation.
Risk of Not Fixing: Phished/leaked passwords give attackers single-factor entry. Worst case: Privileged user phished → attacker logs in unchallenged → bulk data exfil.

Prerequisites: Successful phish/leak • Privileged data access • No anomaly detection


Audit Exception: Phased rollout in progress, [X%] complete. IP allowlisting + shorter session timeouts as compensating controls. 100% target by [date].

