🟢 Group 1: Quick Wins
#8 — ACCOUNTADMIN/SECURITYADMIN granted to a custom role

Severity: High | Scanner: CIS Benchmarks
Current State: Admin role granted into a custom role, contaminating the inheritance chain. Every member of that custom role is silently a superuser. Like leaving the company seal in a shared drawer.
Remediation:

SHOW GRANTS OF ROLE ACCOUNTADMIN / SECURITYADMIN
Identify offending custom roles
REVOKE ROLE ACCOUNTADMIN FROM ROLE <custom_role>
Redesign custom role with least-privilege grants
Validate impacted user workflows


Difficulty: Easy — one REVOKE, but confirm blast radius first
Side-Effect Score: 4/10
Remediation Risk: Users relying on inherited privileges lose access. Worst case: Admin can't perform emergency ops mid-incident.
Risk of Not Fixing: Massive least-privilege violation. Worst case: A user who should have read-only inadvertently or maliciously drops a database.

Prerequisites: Custom role granted broadly • User aware of inherited power • No DDL alerting


Audit Exception: Custom role granted only to [N] core DBAs who legitimately need admin access. Dedicated admin role under design, completion by [date].

