#10 — Authentication key pairs not rotated every 180 days

Severity: Medium | Scanner: CIS Benchmarks
Current State: Service account RSA key pairs older than 180 days. Like expired bento — looks fine, risk grows daily.
Remediation:

Build rotation automation (script/scheduler)
Generate new RSA key pair
ALTER USER ... SET RSA_PUBLIC_KEY_2='<new_key>' (Snowflake supports dual keys)
Switch app to new private key
Unset old key after validation
Schedule recurring 180-day rotation


Difficulty: Med — upfront automation effort, then hands-off
Side-Effect Score: 3/10
Remediation Risk: Botched rotation can briefly break auth. Worst case: Buggy script unsets old key before new key is set → service account fully locked out.
Risk of Not Fixing: Stale keys give attackers a long exploitation window if leaked. Worst case: Private key accidentally committed to public Git repo, undetected for months due to no rotation cadence.

Prerequisites: Poor key storage hygiene • No key-usage anomaly detection • Slow leak discovery


Audit Exception: Current keys under [X] days old; rotation scheduled next maintenance window. Automation pipeline launching [date]. Private keys stored in secrets manager.

