#14 — Users with ACCOUNTADMIN/SECURITYADMIN as default role

Severity: Medium | Scanner: CIS Benchmarks
Current State: Some users have DEFAULT_ROLE set to ACCOUNTADMIN/SECURITYADMIN — they operate at max privilege every session. Like carrying nuclear launch keys to buy breakfast.
Remediation:

SHOW USERS filter by DEFAULT_ROLE
ALTER USER <user> SET DEFAULT_ROLE = '<appropriate_role>'
Establish lower-privilege functional role for daily work
Train users to USE ROLE ACCOUNTADMIN only when needed
Consider session policies to time-bound elevated role usage


Difficulty: Easy — one ALTER USER per account
Side-Effect Score: 2/10
Remediation Risk: Users may forget to elevate when needed. Worst case: Admin loses time mid-incident switching roles.
Risk of Not Fixing: Every routine action runs with full admin power; any fat-finger has account-wide impact. Worst case: Untested DROP/DELETE wipes a production database.

Prerequisites: Lack of pre-change verification • No DDL approval workflow • Weak backup recovery


Audit Exception: Only [N] senior DBAs affected, all trained on privileged account management. Adjustment scheduled for next maintenance window; role-switching SOP being documented.


